  "commentary": "With SPX at 7087.35 sitting just below the 7096 GEX flip, dealers are in positive gamma territory and likely providing liquidity by selling into any strength toward the massive 7100 (+4.9B) and 7200 (+7.2B) gamma walls while buying any dips toward 7040 support. The PIN regime with 43B in total GEX creates a strong mean-reverting environment, suggesting any breakout attempts will face heavy dealer resistance at these key strikes. Watch for choppy action between 7040-7100 with dealers capping upside momentum into the dense gamma wall cluster above.\n\nBottom line: expect the market to get pinned between 7040 and 7100 with limited directional movement.",
